as a maximum date of {{ maxDate }} but is currently set to {{ date }}&q;,&q;ethz.availability.suggest-label&q;:&q;Availability&q;,&q;ethz.book.title.suggest-label&q;:&q;Book Title&q;,&q;ethz.code.ddc.suggest-label&q;:&q;Subject area&q;,&q;ethz.code.jel.suggest-label&q;:&q;JEL Classification&q;,&q;ethz.date.collected.suggest-label&q;:&q;Date Collected&q;,&q;ethz.date.embargoend.suggest-label&q;:&q;Embargo End Date&q;,&q;ethz.date.retentionend.suggest-label&q;:&q;Retention Period End Date&q;,&q;ethz.description.methods.suggest-label&q;:&q;Methods&q;,&q;ethz.description.software.suggest-label&q;:&q;Software&q;,&q;ethz.doipreview.suggest-label&q;:&q;DOI Preview&q;,&q;ethz.edit.notes.suggest-label&q;:&q;Edit Notes&q;,&q;ethz.edit.source.suggest-label&q;:&q;Pub found in&q;,&q;ethz.edit.status.suggest-label&q;:&q;Editing Status&q;,&q;ethz.eth.suggest-label&q;:&q;ETH Publication&q;,&q;ethz.event.suggest-label&q;:&q;Event&q;,&q;ethz.event.date.suggest-label&q;:&q;Event Date&q;,&q;ethz.event.location.suggest-label&q;:&q;Event Location&q;,&q;ethz.geolocation.suggest-label&q;:&q;Geolocation&q;,&q;ethz.grant.suggest-label&q;:&q;Project / Grant&q;,&q;ethz.identifier.suggest-label&q;:&q;Other Identifier&q;,&q;ethz.identifier.diss.suggest-label&q;:&q;Dissertation Number&q;,&q;ethz.identifier.internal.suggest-label&q;:&q;Internal Identifier&q;,&q;ethz.identifier.patent.suggest-label&q;:&q;Patent Number&q;,&q;ethz.journal.issue.suggest-label&q;:&q;Issue Number&q;,&q;ethz.journal.title.suggest-label&q;:&q;Journal or Series Title&q;,&q;ethz.journal.volume.suggest-label&q;:&q;Volume Number&q;,&q;ethz.leitzahl.suggest-label&q;:&q;Organisational Unit&q;,&q;ethz.libdrive.url.suggest-label&q;:&q;Libdrive data URL&q;,&q;ethz.notes.suggest-label&q;:&q;Additional Notes&q;,&q;ethz.pages.end.suggest-label&q;:&q;End Page&q;,&q;ethz.pages.start.suggest-label&q;:&q;Start Page / Article Number&q;,&q;ethz.publication.place.suggest-label&q;:&q;Publication Place&q;,&q;ethz.publication.status.suggest-label&q;:&q;Publication Status&q;,&q;ethz.relation.suggest-label&q;:&q;Related Publications or Datasets&q;,&q;ethz.repository.suggest-label&q;:&q;Data Repository&q;,&q;ethz.size.suggest-label&q;:&q;Size&q;,&q;ethz.tag.suggest-label&q;:&q;Tag&q;,&q;dc.contributor.researchGroup.suggest-label&q;:&q;Research Group&q;,&q;dc.contributor.projectLeader.suggest-label&q;:&q;Project Leader&q;,&q;dc.contributor.projectManager.suggest-label&q;:&q;Project Manager&q;,&q;dc.contributor.projectMember.suggest-label&q;:&q;Project Member&q;,&q;dc.contributor.relatedPerson.suggest-label&q;:&q;Related Person&q;,&q;dc.contributor.rightsHolder.suggest-label&q;:&q;Rights Holder&q;,&q;dc.contributor.contactPerson.suggest-label&q;:&q;Contact Person&q;,&q;dc.contributor.dataCollector.suggest-label&q;:&q;Data Collector&q;,&q;ethz.title.subtitle.suggest-label&q;:&q;Subtitle&q;,&q;ethz.version.suggest-label&q;:&q;Edition / Version&q;,&q;ethz.version.deposit.suggest-label&q;:&q;Deposit Version&q;,&q;ethz.version.edition.suggest-label&q;:&q;Edition / Version&q;,&q;suggest.metadata.select-field&q;:&q;Choose a metadata field&q;,&q;item.suggest.empty.metadatafield.error&q;:&q;Please pick a metadata field from the list to add&q;,&q;item.suggest.notfound.metadatafield.error&q;:&q;The selected metadata field could not be found in the registry&q;,&q;item.suggest.notfound.metadatafield.error.subtitle&q;:&q;Please report this issue to an administrator&q;,&q;item.edit.metadata.edit.buttons.virtual.suggest&q;:&q;&q;,&q;header.help&q;:&q;Help&q;,&q;header.repo-name&q;:&q;Research Collection&q;,&q;footer.link.imprint&q;:&q;Imprint&q;,&q;footer.link.terms-of-use&q;:&q;Terms of Use&q;,&q;footer.link.about&q;:&q;About Research Collection&q;,&q;item.page.type&q;:&q;Publication Type&q;,&q;item.page.ethz.eth&q;:&q;ETH Bibliography&q;,&q;item.page.download&q;:&q;Downloads&q;,&q;file-section.open-access&q;:&q;Open access&q;,&q;item.page.rights&q;:&q;Rights / License&q;,&q;item.page.publication-status&q;:&q;Publication status&q;,&q;item.page.external-links&q;:&q;External links&q;,&q;item.page.journal-volume&q;:&q;Volume&q;,&q;item.page.notes&q;:&q;Notes&q;,&q;item.page.journal-pages&q;:&q;Pages / Article No.&q;,&q;item.page.label.full&q;:&q;More&q;,&q;journal.page.abbreviated&q;:&q;Abbreviation&q;,&q;file-section.metadata-only&q;:&q;Metadata only&q;,&q;file-section.availability.metadata-only&q;:&q;METADATA ONLY&q;,&q;file-section.availability.open-access&q;:&q;OPEN ACCESS&q;,&q;file-section.availability.closed-access&q;:&q;CLOSED ACCESS&q;,&q;file-section.availability.embargoed&q;:&q;EMBARGOED&q;,&q;file-section.availability.embargoed-until&q;:&q;EMBARGOED UNTIL {{date}}&q;,&q;file-section.availability.ethz-users&q;:&q;ACCESS FOR ETH MEMBERS ONLY&q;,&q;file-section.availability.selected-users&q;:&q;SELECTED USERS&q;,&q;home.news.header&q;:&q;Repository for Publications and Research Data&q;,&q;home.submit.button&q;:&q;Submit&q;,&q;home.manual.button&q;:&q;Manual&q;,&q;home.page.latest.news&q;:&q;News from the ETH Library&q;,&q;home.page.latest.empty&q;:&q;No news items to show.&q;,&q;home.page.latest.error&q;:&q;Cannot display new items&q;,&q;author.overflow.text&q;:&q;; et al.&q;,&q;info.terms-of-use.title&q;:&q;Terms of Use&q;,&q;info.terms-of-use.breadcrumbs&q;:&q;Terms of Use&q;,&q;terms-of-use.title&q;:&q;Terms of use&q;,&q;terms-of-use.introduction&q;:&q;Introduction&q;,&q;terms-of-use.introduction-paragraph&q;:&q;The Research Collection is an ETH-Library service and ETH Zurich&s;s publication platform. It offers the following features:&q;,&q;terms-of-use.publication-database&q;:&q;Publication database&q;,&q;terms-of-use.publication-database-paragraph&q;:&q;The Research Collection is a comprehensive database that registers the publications produced at ETH Zurich. It is the source for publication lists&q;,&q;terms-of-use.publication-database-li1&q;:&q;in ETH Zurich&s;s academic reporting (&l;a href=\&q;https://www.ethz.ch/services/en/finance-and-controlling/ethis.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Annual Academic Achievements&l;/a&g;)&q;,&q;terms-of-use.publication-database-li2&q;:&q;on ETH-Zurich websites maintained using the Content Management System &l;a href=\&q;https://www.ethz.ch/services/en/service/communication/websites.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;AEM&l;/a&g;&q;,&q;terms-of-use.open-access-repository&q;:&q;Open access repository&q;,&q;terms-of-use.open-access-repository-paragraph&q;:&q;The Research Collection is the instrument for implementing &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/134en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;ETH Zurich&s;s open access policy&l;/a&g;. It enables members of ETH Zurich to publish academic full texts outside traditional publishing.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.research-data-repository&q;:&q;Research data repository&q;,&q;terms-of-use.research-data-repository-paragraph&q;:&q;The Research Collection acts as a publication platform and digital archive for all kinds of research output. In accordance with the &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/414.2en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Guidelines for Research Data Management at ETH Zurich&l;/a&g; and the &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/414en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;ETH Zurich Guidelines on scientific integrity&l;/a&g; research data can be&q;,&q;terms-of-use.research-data-repository-li1&q;:&q;published as standalone publication,&q;,&q;terms-of-use.research-data-repository-li2&q;:&q;published as supplementary material to a journal article, doctoral thesis or other text publication,&q;,&q;terms-of-use.research-data-repository-li3&q;:&q;deposited to share with colleagues or external users on request.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.contents&q;:&q;Contents&q;,&q;terms-of-use.contents-li1&q;:&q;The Research Collection contains publications and other research output by members of staff and selected works by students from ETH Zurich (cf. &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/8AeSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;list of publication types&l;/a&g;).&q;,&q;terms-of-use.contents-li2&q;:&q;New references are imported from bibliographic databases (currently Web of Science and Scopus) once a day. Moreover, members of staff at ETH Zurich can enter new research output independently at any time.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.contents-li3&q;:&q;Research output that members of staff published before they joined ETH Zurich is marked accordingly in the metadata.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.contents-li4&q;:&q;A digital object in the Research Collection might be an original work or a self-archived copy of an already published work.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use&q;:&q;Access and re-use&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li1&q;:&q;Anyone can access bibliographic data (metadata) in the Research Collection.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li2&q;:&q;Publications and research data can either be accessed via a digital object available in the Research Collection or via a link on an external publisher&s;s website/repository.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li3&q;:&q;The following options are available to access the digital objects:&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li3-li1&q;:&q;Open access: freely accessible&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li3-li2&q;:&q;Embargoed: freely accessible after a stipulated embargo&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li3-li3&q;:&q;ETHZ users: accessible for registered users from ETH Zurich&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li3-li4&q;:&q;Selected users: only accessible for a particular group of users defined by the submitter&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li3-li5&q;:&q;Closed access: only deposited for archiving purposes and only accessible for administrators&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li4&q;:&q;It is possible to apply to access research data with access restrictions. ETH Library forwards release applications to the work&s;s copyright holder, provided that he or she is still employed by ETH Zurich or has an ORCID record with an up-to-date email address.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li5&q;:&q;A full-text search browses the contents of all documents regardless of access rights. Documents with restricted access are also searched.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li6&q;:&q;If no special end user licence is stipulated, the users may download and save the objects on offer free of charge for their own personal use and for non-commercial purposes. Any further use is only possible with the permission of the rights holder.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li7&q;:&q;All metadata are available for reuse under a &l;a href=\&q;https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Public Domain Dedication (CC0)&l;/a&g; and may be used, modified and redistributed without prior consent.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.access-and-re-use-li8&q;:&q;For abstracts, the reuse conditions mentioned in the respective item under \&q;Rights / license\&q; apply. If no such rights notice is available, the abstracts may only be used for personal use.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.responsibility-for-the-content-quality-standards&q;:&q;Responsibility for the content/quality standards&q;,&q;terms-of-use.responsibility-for-the-content-quality-standards-li1&q;:&q;The authenticity and academic quality of the full texts and other digital objects are the sole responsibility of the copyright holders.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.responsibility-for-the-content-quality-standards-li2&q;:&q;The copyright holders agree to observe the &l;a href=\&q;https://ethz.ch/content/dam/ethz/main/research/Ethische%20Fragen/Forschung%20an%20und%20mit%20Menschen/Compliance_Guide_RSETHZ133en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;ETH-Zurich Compliance Guide&l;/a&g; and the provisions and ethical standards stipulated in the &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/414en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;ETH Zurich Guidelines on scientific integrity&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.responsibility-for-the-content-quality-standards-li3&q;:&q;The electronic version of a submitted examination paper (Habilitation Thesis, Doctoral Thesis, Master or Bachelor Thesis) must correspond to the printed version accepted by the examination boards.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.responsibility-for-the-content-quality-standards-li4&q;:&q;Semester, Bachelor and Master Theses as well as Student Papers will only be published with the consent of the supervisor.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.responsibility-for-the-content-quality-standards-li5&q;:&q;The upload of strictly confidential research data, non-anonymised health-related personal data and unpublished research data subject to export control is prohibited. The classification of the data is the responsibility of the researchers.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.responsibility-for-the-content-quality-standards-li6&q;:&q;Software developed at ETH Zurich must be registered with ETH transfer via the &l;a href=\&q;https://ethz.ch/en/industry/researchers/licensing-software.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Software Disclosure Process&l;/a&g; before publication in the Research Collection.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation&q;:&q;Data entry and scope of the work&s;s utilisation&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li1&q;:&q;All members of staff at ETH Zurich are entitled to enter bibliographical references in the Research Collection.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li2&q;:&q;Full texts and research data have to be uploaded by the copyright/rights holder or an authorised representative.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li3&q;:&q;In accordance with the &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/134en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;ETH Zurich&s;s open access policy&l;/a&g;, members of ETH-Zurich staff are required to publish their research results in a freely accessible way. Thus, publications can be submitted using the open access mode – if necessary, applying an embargo.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li4&q;:&q;When submitting research data, the access modes ETHZ users, selected users and closed access (see above) can be selected.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li5&q;:&q;Doctoral Theses are published based on the &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/340.31en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Ordinance on the Doctorate at the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich&l;/a&g; (version: 1 January 2022) and their &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/340.311en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Implementation Provisions of 23 November 2021&l;/a&g; (version: 1 January 2022).&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li6&q;:&q;Doctoral theses published in full are made available to the National Library for archiving and consultation on its premises.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li7&q;:&q;Habilitation Theses are published based on the &l;a href=\&q;https://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/20041257/200808010000/414.110.373.1.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Habilitation Ordinance from 2 June 2004&l;/a&g; (version: 1 August 2008).&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li8&q;:&q;The publication of open source software is based on the &l;a href=\&q;https://ethz.ch/content/dam/ethz/main/industry/researcher/ETH_Zurich_Exploitation_Guidelines.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Guidelines for the Financial Exploitation of Research Results at ETH Zurich&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li9&q;:&q;ETH Library receives permission to publish and/or archive the digital object in the Research Collection. It is authorised to save and archive the object and the associated metadata on ETH Zurich&s;s servers, extract summaries of examination papers, alter and/or enrich the object&s;s metadata and pass it on to third parties, and take measures for long-term, digital archiving, including migration into new file formats.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-entry-and-scope-of-the-works-utilisation-li10&q;:&q;Rights holders can stipulate how their works are allowed to be re-used, for example by publishing them under a Creative Commons licence or an Open Source licence. ETH Library explicitly recommends choosing open licences. The licence selected must be integrated in the work. Moreover, it appears on the landing page.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks&q;:&q;Internal processing procedure and copyright checks&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks-li1&q;:&q;All entries undergo an internal processing procedure. ETH Library checks new publications for the&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks-li1-li1&q;:&q;Consistency and completeness of the metadata&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks-li1-li2&q;:&q;Legibility of full texts and other digital objects&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks-li1-li3&q;:&q;Relevance of the contents for the Research Collection&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks-li1-li4&q;:&q;Observance of possible legal norms (copyright and self-archiving guidelines of the publishing houses)&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks-li2&q;:&q;The metadata of all publications is directly visible after data entry and can be searched. Digital objects (full texts and research data) are not visible until the internal processing procedure has been completed.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.internal-processing-procedure-and-copyright-checks-li3&q;:&q;Publications for which the processing procedure is not yet complete are displayed with a message to this effect.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.content-related-changes-to-bibliographical-data-and-digital-objects&q;:&q;Content-related changes to bibliographical data and digital objects&q;,&q;terms-of-use.content-related-changes-to-bibliographical-data-and-digital-objects-li1&q;:&q;Changes to bibliographical data can be requested via the button \&q;Suggest edit\&q;.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.content-related-changes-to-bibliographical-data-and-digital-objects-li2&q;:&q;To guarantee citability, content-related changes to full texts and research data that have already been published are not possible.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.content-related-changes-to-bibliographical-data-and-digital-objects-li3&q;:&q;New versions of full texts and research data that have already been published can only be uploaded by the rights holders/authorised people and linked to the earlier version published. The same goes for errata and corrigenda.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.content-related-changes-to-bibliographical-data-and-digital-objects-li4&q;:&q;After the electronic version of an examination paper (Bachelor or Master Thesis, Doctoral Thesis, Habilitation Thesis) has been submitted and published via Research Collection, it can no longer be exchanged. It is only possible to add errata or corrigenda to the work.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods&q;:&q;Restriction of the accessibility of objects and retention periods&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li1&q;:&q;In principle, digital objects that have already been published are not deleted from the Research Collection. In exceptional cases, a digital object&s;s accessibility can be restricted if evidence is provided.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li2&q;:&q;ETH Library takes such an exception into consideration if evidence of one of the following issues is provided:&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li2-li1&q;:&q;Copyright infringement&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li2-li2&q;:&q;Infringement of the &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/414en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;ETH Zurich Guidelines on scientific integrity&l;/a&g;&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li2-li3&q;:&q;Infringement of confidentiality obligations&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li2-li4&q;:&q;Retraction by the publishing house&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li3&q;:&q;Applications to restrict accessibility are to be made to: &l;a href=\&q;mailto:research-collection@library.ethz.ch\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;research-collection@library.ethz.ch&l;/a&g;&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li4&q;:&q;If there is a justified exception, the digital object is withdrawn. The landing page with the bibliographical information on the object remains freely accessible and indicates the date of and reason for the change.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li5&q;:&q;For research data, a restricted retention period of ten or 15 years can be agreed. ETH Library reserves the right to delete digital objects once the stipulated retention period has elapsed without further consultation.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.restriction-of-the-accessibility-of-objects-and-retention-periods-li6&q;:&q;The guaranteed retention period for research data published via the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/HQiSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;libdrive&l;/a&g; service is 10 years.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.long-term-archiving&q;:&q;Long-term archiving&q;,&q;terms-of-use.long-term-archiving-li1&q;:&q;All objects available in the Research Collection are saved unchanged and stored long-term in the ETH Data Archive.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.long-term-archiving-li2&q;:&q;Where possible, the usability of data available in a standard file format is guaranteed for the long term. The selection of suitable formats facilitates this process. See the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/8QeSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;File-format recommendations for archiving&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.long-term-archiving-li3&q;:&q;Research data published via the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/HQiSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;libdrive&l;/a&g; service are not archived in the ETH Data Archive.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.long-term-archiving-li4&q;:&q;Data that enters the ETH Data Archive from the Research Collection is only accessible there for library staff members.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.technical-operation&q;:&q;Technical operation&q;,&q;terms-of-use.technical-operation-li1&q;:&q;The Research Collection&s;s IT platform is operated by ETH Library&s;s Digital Business Solutions Group in collaboration with ETH Zurich&s;s IT Services. The goal is a system availability of 99.5% during normal operating hours. Application and infrastructure updates are made within the scope of announced maintenance windows. The technical operator strives to ensure that the platform works properly around the clock (best effort), but guarantees neither the uninterrupted usability nor accessibility of the platform, nor is liable for technical transmission delays or breakdowns.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.technical-operation-li2&q;:&q;The operator reserves the right to change or discontinue Research Collection functions without prior notice, if required by operational necessity. Moreover, the operator is entitled to assign operational, development or support services to third parties in part or in full at any time with or without giving reasons.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-protection&q;:&q;Data protection&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-protection-li1&q;:&q;Personal data is stored and processed in accordance with the ETH Library&s;s &l;a href=\&q;https://library.ethz.ch/en/footer/data-protection.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;data protection declaration&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.data-protection-li2&q;:&q;When uploading personal or other potentially sensitive data, the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/XQiSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;guidelines for handling sensitive data&l;/a&g; must be observed.&q;,&q;terms-of-use.status-date&q;:&q;Status: August 2025&q;,&q;info.feedback.instructions-and-faqs.head&q;:&q;Instructions and FAQs&q;,&q;info.feedback.instructions-and-faqs.before-link&q;:&q;Answers to Frequently Asked Questions as well as step-by-step instructions for key features can be found in the &q;,&q;info.feedback.instructions-and-faqs.link&q;:&q;Research Collection Manual&q;,&q;info.feedback.instructions-and-faqs.after-link&q;:&q;.&q;,&q;info.feedback.name-label&q;:&q;Name: *&q;,&q;info.feedback.name_help&q;:&q;This name will be used to follow up on your feedback.&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.head&q;:&q;Our address and phone number:&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.eth-zurich&q;:&q;ETH Zurich&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.eth-bibliothek&q;:&q;ETH-Bibliothek&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.e-publishing&q;:&q;E-Publishing&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.research-collection&q;:&q;Research Collection&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.street&q;:&q;Rämistrasse 101&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.city&q;:&q;8092 Zürich&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.phone-number&q;:&q;Tel: +41 44 632 72 22&q;,&q;info.feedback.address-and-number.email-address&q;:&q;research-collection@library.ethz.ch&q;,&q;info.imprint.title&q;:&q;Imprint&q;,&q;info.imprint.breadcrumbs&q;:&q;Imprint&q;,&q;imprint.title&q;:&q;Imprint&q;,&q;imprint.p1&q;:&q;ETH Zurich&q;,&q;imprint.p2&q;:&q;ETH Library&q;,&q;imprint.p3&q;:&q;Rämistrasse 101&q;,&q;imprint.p4&q;:&q;8092 Zurich&q;,&q;imprint.p5&q;:&q;Switzerland&q;,&q;imprint.p6&q;:&q;&l;a href=\&q;https://www.library.ethz.ch/en/\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q; class=\&q;hrefLink\&q;&g;https://www.library.ethz.ch&l;/a&g;&q;,&q;imprint.publisher&q;:&q;Publisher&q;,&q;imprint.publisher.p1&q;:&q;Dr. Rafael Ball, Director ETH-Bibliothek&q;,&q;imprint.editorial-office&q;:&q;Editorial office&q;,&q;imprint.editorial-office.p1&q;:&q;Barbara Hirschmann, ETH Library&q;,&q;imprint.system-responsibility&q;:&q;System responsibility&q;,&q;imprint.system-responsibility.p1&q;:&q;Digital Business Solutions, ETH Library&q;,&q;imprint.software&q;:&q;Software&q;,&q;imprint.front-page-image&q;:&q;Front page image&q;,&q;imprint.front-page-image.p1&q;:&q;Andrea Testa: Surface tension induced-flow in a protein droplet&q;,&q;imprint.contact&q;:&q;Contact&q;,&q;info.about.title&q;:&q;About&q;,&q;info.about.breadcrumbs&q;:&q;About&q;,&q;about.title&q;:&q;About Research Collection&q;,&q;about.title-p1&q;:&q;The Research Collection is ETH Zurich&s;s repository for publications and research data.&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database&q;:&q;Institutional Publications Database&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-p1&q;:&q;The Research Collection provides a comprehensive database of scholarly publications produced at ETH Zurich. It is the source for publication lists&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li1&q;:&q;in ETH Zurich&s;s academic reporting database &l;a href=\&q;https://www.ethz.ch/services/en/finance-and-controlling/ethis.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Annual Academic Achievements&l;/a&g;,&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li2&q;:&q;on ETH Zurich&s;s websites maintained with &l;a href=\&q;https://www.ethz.ch/services/en/service/communication/websites.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;AEM&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-p2&q;:&q;Feature highlights:&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li3&q;:&q;Submit new references &l;b&g;\&q;with a single click\&q;&l;/b&g; (via DOI request)&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li4&q;:&q;Display of &l;b&g;\&q;Cited by\&q; counts&l;/b&g; and &l;b&g;Altmetrics&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li5&q;:&q;Author identifiers (&l;b&g;ORCID iDs&l;/b&g;)&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li6&q;:&q;Continuous import of new references from &l;b&g;Web of Science&l;/b&g; and &l;b&g;Scopus&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li7&q;:&q;Continuous &l;b&g;enhancement&l;/b&g; and &l;b&g;correction&l;/b&g; of metadata by professional librarians&q;,&q;about.institutional-publications-database-li8&q;:&q;Can be connected to further systems via &l;b&g;standardized interfaces&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository&q;:&q;Open Access Repository&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-p1&q;:&q;The Research Collection is the application to implement &l;a href=\&q;https://ethz.ch/en/research/open-science/open-access.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;ETH Zurich&s;s open-access policy&l;/a&g;. It allows members of ETH Zurich to publish scholarly works outside traditional publishing.&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-p2&q;:&q;Feature highlights:&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-li1&q;:&q;&l;b&g;DOIs&l;/b&g; for all publications, &l;b&g;DOI reservation&l;/b&g; possible&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-li2&q;:&q;Up-to-date &l;b&g;download statistics&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-li3&q;:&q;Display of &l;b&g;journal copyright policies&l;/b&g; in the submission workflow&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-li4&q;:&q;Automatic &l;b&g;embargo handling&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-li5&q;:&q;Indexed in &l;b&g;Google Scholar&l;/b&g; and other search engines&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-li6&q;:&q;Connect publications with &l;b&g;Grant IDs&l;/b&g; so they will be displayed in the European Commission&s;s &l;b&g;OpenAIRE&l;/b&g; portal&q;,&q;about.open-access-repository-li7&q;:&q;Connection with ETH Data Archive provides for secure &l;b&g;long term preservation&l;/b&g; of all publications&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository&q;:&q;Research Data Repository&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p1&q;:&q;The Research Collection provides to members of ETH Zurich a publication platform and digital archive for all types of research output. In accordance with ETH Zurich&s;s &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/414.2en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Guidelines for Research Data Management&l;/a&g;, research data can be&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p1-li1&q;:&q;published as standalone publication,&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p1-li2&q;:&q;published as supplementary material to a journal article, dissertation or other text publication,&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p1-li3&q;:&q;deposited to be shared with the ETH community or with external users upon request&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2&q;:&q;Feature highlights:&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li1&q;:&q;&l;b&g;Flexible access rights&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li2&q;:&q;&l;b&g;DOIs&l;/b&g; for all published data, &l;b&g;DOI reservation&l;/b&g; possible&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li3&q;:&q;Automatic &l;b&g;embargo handling&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li4&q;:&q;Content &l;b&g;preview&l;/b&g; for ZIP- and tar-containers&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li5&q;:&q;&l;b&g;Temporary retention&l;/b&g; of data for 10 or 15 years possible&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li6&q;:&q;Up-to-date &l;b&g;download statistics&l;/b&g;&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li7&q;:&q;Connect research data with &l;b&g;Grant IDs&l;/b&g; so they will be displayed in the European Commission&s;s &l;b&g;OpenAIRE&l;/b&g; portal&q;,&q;about.research-data-repository-p2-li8&q;:&q;Connection with ETH Data Archive provides for secure &l;b&g;long term preservation&l;/b&g; of all research data publications up to 50 GB&q;,&q;about.further-information&q;:&q;Further information&q;,&q;about.further-information-p1&q;:&q;Answers to Frequently Asked Questions as well as step-by-step instructions for important features can be found on the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/display/RC/Research+Collection\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;Research Collection Manual&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;about.certification&q;:&q;Certification&q;,&q;about.certification-p1&q;:&q;The Research Collection is certified by &l;a href=\&q;https://www.coretrustseal.org/\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q; rel=\&q;noopener noreferrer\&q;&g;CoreTrustSeal&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;client.submission.disclaimer.20.500.11850/34&q;:&q;&l;p&g;All software developed at ETH Zurich and made available to third parties (e.g. through the Research Collection) &l;strong&g;must be reported to ETH transfer&l;/strong&g; (see &l;a href=\&q;https://ethz.ch/content/dam/ethz/main/industry/researcher/ETH_Zurich_Exploitation_Guidelines.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;Guidelines for the Financial Exploitation of Research Results at ETH Zurich&l;/a&g;). Open Source Software only needs a registration with the ETH Data Archive. &l;/p&g; &l;p&g;&l;strong&g;Please ensure that the software is licensed and registered correctly before publication in the Research Collection.&l;/strong&g; More information can be found in the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/6AeSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;Manual&l;/a&g;&l;/p&g;&l;/i18n:message&g;&q;,&q;client.submission.disclaimer.20.500.11850/19&q;:&q;&l;p&g;For the publication of a bachelor&s;s thesis a &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/display/RC/Master%2C+Bachelor+and+Semester+Theses%2C+Student+Papers?preview=%2F194119870%2F194120225%2F2023-05-03_Declaration_of_Consent_1.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;declaration of consent&l;/a&g; from the author &l;strong&g;and&l;/strong&g; the supervisor is required. As soon as you have finished the submission, please send the completed and signed declaration immediately to &l;a href=\&q;mailto:research-collection@library.ethz.ch\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;research-collection@library.ethz.ch&l;/a&g;. More information can be found in the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/vgiSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;Manual&l;/a&g;.&l;/p&g;&q;,&q;client.submission.disclaimer.20.500.11850/18&q;:&q;&l;p&g;For the publication of a master&s;s thesis a &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/display/RC/Master%2C+Bachelor+and+Semester+Theses%2C+Student+Papers?preview=%2F194119870%2F194120225%2F2023-05-03_Declaration_of_Consent_1.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;declaration of consent&l;/a&g; from the author &l;strong&g;and&l;/strong&g; the supervisor is required. As soon as you have finished the submission, please send the completed and signed declaration immediately to &l;a href=\&q;mailto:research-collection@library.ethz.ch\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;research-collection@library.ethz.ch&l;/a&g;. More information can be found in the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/vgiSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;Manual&l;/a&g;.&l;/p&g;&q;,&q;client.submission.disclaimer.20.500.11850/27&q;:&q;&l;p&g;For the publication of a semester thesis or student paper a &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/display/RC/Master%2C+Bachelor+and+Semester+Theses%2C+Student+Papers?preview=%2F194119870%2F194120225%2F2023-05-03_Declaration_of_Consent_1.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;declaration of consent&l;/a&g; from the author &l;strong&g;and&l;/strong&g; the supervisor is required. As soon as you have finished the submission, please send the completed and signed declaration immediately to &l;a href=\&q;mailto:research-collection@library.ethz.ch\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;research-collection@library.ethz.ch&l;/a&g;. More information can be found in the &l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/vgiSCw\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;Manual&l;/a&g;.&l;/p&g;&q;,&q;client.submission.disclaimer.20.500.11850/16&q;:&q;&l;p&g;Please design the title page of your doctoral thesis in accordance with the &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/340.311en.pdf\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;Rector’s Implementation Provisions for the ETH Zurich Ordinance on the Doctorate of ETH Zurich&l;/a&g; (example cover page see page 17). More information can be found on the website of the &l;a href=\&q;https://ethz.ch/students/en/doctorate/doctoral-thesis-examination.html\&q; target=\&q;_blank\&q;&g;Doctoral Administration Office&l;/a&g;.&l;/p&g;&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.breadcrumbs&q;:&q;Confirm Organisational Codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.certify&q;:&q;Confirm selected codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.clear&q;:&q;Clear selection&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.dismissed-button.include&q;:&q;Include dismissed codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.dismissed-button.exclude&q;:&q;Exclude dismissed codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.description1&q;:&q;The following list shows all Publications or Research Data which were attributed to an organisational unit you are responsible for. Since every ETH Zurich user can attribute a publication to his or her organisational unit, any attribution needs to be confirmed by you in order for the publication to be included in the Annual Academic Achievements.&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.description2&q;:&q;Confirm a code by selecting the checkbox next to it. Confirm your selection by clicking \&q;Certify selected codes\&q;. Use the search input to filter the items.&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.authorised&q;:&q;These are the organisation codes you are responsible for:&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.dismiss&q;:&q;Dismiss selected codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.error.certify&q;:&q;Failed to certify organisation codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.error.dismiss&q;:&q;Failed to dismiss organisation codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.error.empty-body&q;:&q;No organisation codes selected. Please select organisation codes before performing an action.&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.error.header&q;:&q;Error&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.success.certify&q;:&q;Successfully certified organisational unit&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.success.dismiss&q;:&q;Successfully dismissed organisational unit&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.success.header&q;:&q;Success&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.title&q;:&q;Confirm Organisational Codes&q;,&q;leitzahl.validation.unauthorised&q;:&q;You are not authorised for any organisational units.&q;,&q;menu.section.leitzahl-validation&q;:&q;Organisational Code Validation&q;,&q;publication.component.access.files&q;:&q;Access the files&q;,&q;publication.component.data&q;:&q;Data&q;,&q;publication.component.dc.contributor.*&q;:&q;Contributors&q;,&q;publication.component.*.book.title&q;:&q;Book title&q;,&q;publication.component.*.event&q;:&q;Event&q;,&q;publication.component.*.version.edition&q;:&q;Edition / version&q;,&q;publication.component.*.description.method&q;:&q;Methods&q;,&q;publication.component.*.description.software&q;:&q;Software&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.advisor&q;:&q;Advisor&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.contactPerson&q;:&q;Contact person&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.dataCollector&q;:&q;Data collector&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.illustrator&q;:&q;Illustrator&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.other&q;:&q;Other&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.producer&q;:&q;Producer&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.projectLeader&q;:&q;Project leader&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.projectManager&q;:&q;Project manager&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.projectMember&q;:&q;Project member&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.relatedPerson&q;:&q;Related person&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.researchGroup&q;:&q;Research group&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.researcher&q;:&q;Researcher&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.rightsHolder&q;:&q;Rights holder&q;,&q;publication.component.contributors.supervisor&q;:&q;Examiner&q;,&q;publication.page.date.collected&q;:&q;Date collected&q;,&q;publication.page.date.created&q;:&q;Date created&q;,&q;publication.page.org&q;:&q;Organisational unit&q;,&q;geolocation.placename.component.title&q;:&q;Geographic location&q;,&q;geolocation.placename.component.placename&q;:&q;Place name&q;,&q;geolocation.placename.component.coordinates&q;:&q;Point coordinates&q;,&q;geolocation.placename.component.latitude&q;:&q;Latitude&q;,&q;geolocation.placename.component.longitude&q;:&q;Longitude&q;,&q;publication.component.dc.contributor.editor&q;:&q;Editor&q;,&q;browse.comcol.by.leitzahl&q;:&q;By Organisational Units&q;,&q;browse.heading&q;:&q;Value&q;,&q;browse.heading.author&q;:&q;Name&q;,&q;item-alerts.ethz-status.QS1&q;:&q;This record is in review state, the data has not yet been validated.&q;,&q;item-alerts.ethz-status.QS2&q;:&q;This record has been edited as far as possible, missing data will be added when the version of record is issued.&q;,&q;item-alerts.ethz-status.QS3&q;:&q;This record is in review state.&q;,&q;item-alerts.ethz-status.QS4&q;:&q;This record is in review state.&q;,&q;item-alerts.ethz-status.QSN&q;:&q;Not to be approved. Record could not be verified.&q;,&q;item-versions-notice.has-version-QA&q;:&q;A more recent version of this item is in the workflow of &l;a href=\&q;mailto:{{ email }}\&q;&g;{{ email }}&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;item-versions-notice.has-version-non-QA&q;:&q;A more recent version of this item is in the workflow of a user.&