sue&q;:&q;Issue Number&q;,&q;item.preview.ethz.journal.volume&q;:&q;Issue volume&q;,&q;browse.taxonomy_leitzahl-search.intro-text&q;:&q;&l;p&g;Check the boxes next to the organisational units that you wish to browse to and click on the “Search” button. This will deliver all publications from the selected units including their sub-units.&l;/p&g;&l;p&g;To find a certain unit in the organisational structure, enter the name or the code in the Filter field.&l;/p&g;&q;,&q;compressed-file-display.error.500&q;:&q;Something went wrong retrieving the json file representing the internal structure of this file&q;,&q;rss.subscribe-message&q;:&q;Subscribe&q;,&q;button.expand.all&q;:&q;Open all&q;,&q;button.collapse.all&q;:&q;Close all&q;,&q;intro.text.community.list&q;:&q;Select a publication type to list all items of this type.&q;,&q;sidebar.submit_global&q;:&q;Submit&q;,&q;new.submission.header&q;:&q;New Submission&q;,&q;new.submission.intro&q;:&q;Choose one of the options below to submit a new item. You can import a new publication/research data from an external source, start a new submission by entering metadata, or start a new submission by uploading files.&q;,&q;new.submission.avoid_duplicates.title&q;:&q;Avoid Duplicates&q;,&q;new.submission.avoid_duplicates.info&q;:&q;Before starting a new submission, please check via the search box if your publication is already recorded in the Research Collection. We are constantly importing new ETH publications from external databases. You can &l;a href=&s;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/2AeSCw&s; target=&s;_blank&s; rel=&s;noopener&s;&g;add organizational codes&l;/a&g; to existing items, &l;a href=&s;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/3weSCw&s; target=&s;_blank&s; rel=&s;noopener&s;&g;suggest edits&l;/a&g;, and &l;a href=&s;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/x/4AeSCw&s; target=&s;_blank&s; rel=&s;noopener&s;&g;upload fulltexts&l;/a&g;.&q;,&q;new.submission.option.import.title&q;:&q;Option 1: Import&q;,&q;new.submission.option.import.info&q;:&q;Import publication/research data via DOI, ORCID, arXiv or PubMed:&q;,&q;new.submission.option.new.title&q;:&q;Option 2: New&q;,&q;new.submission.option.new.info&q;:&q;Start a new submission by entering metadata:&q;,&q;new.submission.option.upload.title&q;:&q;Option 3: Upload&q;,&q;new.submission.option.upload.info&q;:&q;Start a new submission by uploading a file:&q;,&q;mydspace.new-submission-external.choose-item-type&q;:&q;Choose a publication type&q;,&q;mydspace.new-submission.choose-item-type&q;:&q;Choose a publication type&q;,&q;dropdown.field.placeholder&q;:&q;Select Option&q;,&q;nav.mydspace.import.ris-bibtex&q;:&q;RIS/BibTex Import&q;,&q;dso.edit.label&q;:&q;Edit&q;,&q;dso.list.label&q;:&q;List&q;,&q;search.form.header&q;:&q;Search&q;,&q;search.filters.namedresourcetype.Archived&q;:&q;Submitted&q;,&q;search.filters.namedresourcetype.item,authority&q;:&q;Submitted&q;,&q;search.filters.namedresourcetype.Workspace&q;:&q;Draft&q;,&q;search.filters.namedresourcetype.workspace,authority&q;:&q;Draft&q;,&q;file-download-link.closed-access&q;:&q;Closed Access&q;,&q;file-download-link.request-access&q;:&q;Request Access&q;,&q;submission.import-external.instructions&q;:&q;Instructions&q;,&q;submission.import-external.instructions.proceed&q;:&q;Please proceed as follows to import from the external sources provided&q;,&q;submission.import-external.instructions.doi&q;:&q;&l;b&g;DOI&l;/b&g;: Enter DOI without URL prefix, e.g. 10.1038/s41467-025-56794-x&q;,&q;submission.import-external.instructions.orcid&q;:&q;&l;b&g;ORCID&l;/b&g;: Enter ORCID iD without URL prefix, e.g. 0000-0003-0826-2980&q;,&q;submission.import-external.instructions.arxiv&q;:&q;&l;b&g;arXiv&l;/b&g;: Enter arXiv iD without version number, e.g. 2505.19304&q;,&q;submission.import-external.instructions.pubmed&q;:&q;&l;b&g;PubMed&l;/b&g;: Enter PMCID or PMID, e.g. PMC7068211 or 32210846&q;,&q;submission.import-external.instructions.hint-search&q;:&q;In the arXiv and PubMed sources, you can also search using the title of the publication.&q;,&q;submission.import-external.start&q;:&q;Start Import&q;,&q;signet.discover&q;:&q;Discover new chapters.&q;,&q;signet.library&q;:&q;ETH Library&q;,&q;header-breadcrumbs.eth-zurich&q;:&q;ETH Zurich&q;,&q;header-breadcrumbs.eth-library&q;:&q;ETH Library&q;,&q;header-breadcrumbs.research-collection&q;:&q;Research Collection&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoReason.label&q;:&q;Reason for applying an embargo&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoReason.hint&q;:&q;Please provide the reason why you request to embargo access your doctoral thesis.&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoReason.required&q;:&q;You must give a reason for the embargo.&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoPeriod.label&q;:&q;Embargo period&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoPeriod.hint&q;:&q;ETH Zurich, via its &l;a href=\&q;https://rechtssammlung.sp.ethz.ch/Dokumente/340.31en.pdf\&q;&g;Ordinance on Doctoral Studies&l;/a&g;, requires all doctoral students to publish their doctoral theses open access.&a;#10;&a;#10;\nDoctoral students might request an embargo of 12, 24, or 36 months on the open access publication.&a;#10;\nHowever, the embargo stipulated here applies only to the electronic version of the doctoral thesis. After expiry of the embargo period, the full text of your doctoral thesis will be made publicly available. Exclusively in the case of embargo requests based on patent applications, a lending restriction of a maximum of twelve months will be imposed on the printed copies.&a;#10;&a;#10;\nIf you request an embargo because you are submitting a cumulative doctoral thesis, please &l;strong&g;check the embargo period for doctoral theses required by your publisher&l;/strong&g;, using the information in the\n&l;a href=\&q;https://unlimited.ethz.ch/spaces/RC/pages/194119680/Research+Collection\&q;&g;Research Collection Manual&l;/a&g;.&a;#10;&a;#10;\nIf you have any questions about publishers’ policies on cumulative doctoral theses, please contact us via\n&l;a href=\&q;mailto:research-collection@library.ethz.ch\&q;&g;research-collection@library.ethz.ch&l;/a&g; or Tel: +41 44 632 72 22.\n&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoPeriod.required&q;:&q;You must specify an embargo period.&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoReason.option.copyright&q;:&q;Copyright reasons (e.g. publisher publications)&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoReason.option.patent_registrations&q;:&q;Patent registrations&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoReason.option.ongoing_applications&q;:&q;Ongoing applications at research funding institutions&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoPeriod.option.1y&q;:&q;12 months&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoPeriod.option.2y&q;:&q;24 months&q;,&q;bitstream.edit.form.doctorateEmbargoPeriod.option.3y&q;:&q;36 months&q;,&q;admin.access-control.groups.form.members-list.search.scope.email&q;:&q;E-mail (exact)&q;,&q;admin.access-control.groups.form.members-list.search.scope.metadata&q;:&q;Metadata&q;,&q;admin.access-control.groups.form.subgroups-list.table.edit.currentGroup&q;:&q;Current group&q;,&q;atmire.saved-item-list.new-list.confirm&q;:&q;Confirm&q;,&q;atmire.saved-item-list.new-list.name.empty&q;:&q;The list&s;s name cannot be empty&q;,&q;atmire.saved-item-list.new-list.name.exists&q;:&q;A list with this name already exists&q;,&q;atmire.selective-export-dropdown.my-list.option.add-all&q;:&q;Add all results to {{ name }}&q;,&q;atmire.selective-export-dropdown.my-list.option.add-all.error.title&q;:&q;An error occurred&q;,&q;atmire.selective-export-dropdown.my-list.option.add-all.success.content&q;:&q;All the current discovery items were successfully added to your list.&q;,&q;atmire.selective-export-dropdown.my-list.option.add-all.success.title&q;:&q;Successfully added all items&q;,&q;submissions.sections.submit.progressbar.duplicates&q;:&q;Potential duplicates&q;}},&q;NGRX_STATE&q;:{&q;router&q;:{&q;state&q;:{&q;url&q;:&q;/entities/researchdata/2ecca65c-bc7b-4e72